\section{Overview x}

\begin{itemize}
\item {\bf Source Verse} is (an approximation of) the full source language.
\item The \emph{superficial-desugar} pass desugars Source Verse into
  {\bf Essential Verse}, whose distinctive feature is TimLambdas.
  Essential Verse is a subset of Source Verse.
\item We have three different approaches to the denotational semantics
  of Essential Source Verse:
  \begin{itemize}
  \item Plan A: a direct denotational semantics. (Not done)
  \item Plan B: desugar into {\bf Destination Passing Style Verse}
    (DpsVerse), then give a semantics to that.
  \item Plan C: desugar into {\bf Mini Verse}, still in expression
    style, and give a semantics to that.
  \end{itemize}
\item The rewrite rules
\item The verification rules
\end{itemize}

